    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1162"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/177</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>A written demand was made on the 15th instant by the Carranza Government on the
                    Banco Internacional Hipotecario, which is a Mexican Company but belongs to an
                    English family named Honey, for 225,000 pesos. No reason or excuse was given. On
                    the following day 125,000 were actually taken.</p>
                <pb facs="1177" n="1011" xml:id="pg_1011"/>
                <p>His Majesty’s Government consider this incident as one of much importance both in
                    itself and for the precedent which it establishes.</p>
                <p>They request the United States Government to concert with them in any action
                    which may appear to the United States Government as likely to be effective.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colville Barclay</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
